 Majidun area of Ikorodu, on the outskirts of Lagos. The buses with registration numbers, FKJ 704 XK and FKJ 864 XV were driving inward Ikorodu using the outward Ikorodu Lane. NAN reports that the two buses and the drivers were handed over to the Divisional Police Officer (DPO) at Owode Onirin police station for necessary actions. Vanguard There is no public agitation against the traffic law. There is overwhelming support for it by Lagosians. Like in any society, those who are against any policy are those who kick. For your information we have document the commercial motorcycle operators signed, it was not forced on them. December 15, 2012 In "Special Report" Commuters in Lagos State groaned yesterday as LAGBUS operators disrupted transport activities in protest against treatment by the stateâ€™s traffic law enforcement agencies. June 20, 2017 In "News" The Lagos State Government, yesterday, sealed off the premises of some major commercial transport companies, at Jibowu, along Ikorodu Road as it commenced enforcement of the relocation order of inter-state buses from Jibowu to designated Ojota area of the state. December 12, 2017 In "News"